      private void displayInfo()

    • setLogPref

      private void setLogPref()
      Sets the preferences for log file locations.

      Log configuration has the highest priority and is invoked in the sole constructor of the Config class. This method is invoked prior to configuration of all other preferences as it is required for the logger to start before all other processes.

    • promptLangPref

      private Language promptLangPref()
      Prompt the user for language preference.

      This method has the highest priority after logger configuration (setLogPref()) in order to configure the necessary resource bundles for localized strings.

      Returns:
      The Language to use for this instance.
      See Also:
      setPreferences()

    • promptTimerPref

      private Timer promptTimerPref()
      Prompt the user for time zone preference.
      Returns:
      The Timer object to use for this instance.
      See Also:
      setPreferences()

    • setPreferences

      public void setPreferences()
      Set the program's preferences.

      Default settings and program's data are loaded from the resource bundle(s). Preferences set by the user are prompted via stdin (language and time zone for this implementation). Note that the language must be configured first in order to determine the resource bundles needed for localized texts.

      See Also:
      promptLangPref()
